name: Frontline
rules: Kill enemy players. The first team to reach the specified number of kills wins! Players respawn at a fixed location after each death.

name: Team Deathmatch
rules: Kill enemy players and take the lead. Be the first to reach the specified number of kills to win.

name: Domination
rules: Two factions compete to capture and hold three locations. Each time an objective is captured, the faction will get 1 point after a period of time; the first team to reach the target score wins.

name: Hardpoint
rules: Two factions compete to capture a Hardpoint. When there are only players from the same faction inside the Hardpoint zone, this faction will score 1 point each second. The hardpoint will relocate to a new position after a period of time. The faction that reaches the specified score limit wins.

name: Search & Destroy
rules: Attacker wins when the bomb is planted and detonated at A/B point or when all enemies are eliminated. There are several rounds. Attackers and Defenders will alternate after a certain number of rounds. The first team to win the target number of rounds wins.

name: Free For All
rules: Each player competes against all other players. The first player to reach the specified number of kills wins.

name: Kill Confirmed
rules: Killed players drop dog tags. Enemy dog tags are outlined in red while friendly dog tags are outlined in blue. Collecting enemy dog tags scores points. The first team to reach target number of dog tags wins. Collecting enemy dog tags confirms the kill. Collecting friendly dog tags denies the enemy's kill.

name: Gunfight
rules: The first team to reach 6 points wins. Eliminating all enemies in the first 40 seconds scors 1 point. After 40 seconds, a targeted area will appear for 10 seconds. Capture the location for a second chance at victory.

name: Payout Search & Destroy
rules: Core gameplay is the same as Search & Destroy. The biggest change in this mode is that weapons and other gear can only be bought with money that players earn. Loadout only contains 1 primary weapon, 1 secondary weapon, 2 tacticals, and 1 lethal grenade. Knife damage adjusted to 75, and it will cause higher damage when jumping. If players survive the last round, and the round will not switch sides, they will keep their loadouts. If they don't, they will lose the loadouts. Both teams play for 5 rounds in each half. After 5 rounds, they switch sides, and their money will reset. The first team to reach 6 scores wins.

name: Control
rules: All players on the team share a limited number of lives. Annihilate the enemy to win this round. The game is divided into multiple rounds. After each round, the attackers and defenders are swapped. The team that meets the requirements for winning first wins the round. If the attacking team captures points A and B before the limit time is reached, they wil win the round. If the defending team prevents points A and B from being captured, they will win the round.

name: Patrol
rules: Two factions compete to capture a Hardpoint. When there are only players from the same faction inside the Hardpoint zone, this faction will score 1 point each second. A mobile capture point will go around the map along the set route. The faction that reaches the specified score limit wins.

name: Gun Game
rules: Each player starts with the same weapon. Every time you kill an enemy with your gun, you're upgraded to the next weapon. The match ends when someone cycles through all twenty weapons.

name: Gun Game: Team Fight
rules: Kill players with given weapons. The first team to reach the score limit or kill with each weapon wins!

name: Snipers Only
rules: Only sniper rifles are allowed in this mode. The first team to reach the score limit wins.

name: Sticks and Stones
rules: Players are equipped with a combat knife and a combat axe. The overall rules are the same as Free For All. The first player to reach the score limit wins.

name: One Shot One Kill
rules: Players are equipped with a .50 GS pistol, adjusted to one-shot kill. The first player to reach the score limit wins.

name: Prop Hunt
rules: The objective is to eliminate the props as a Hunter or survive until the timer expires as a Prop. The player who is in the Top 3 wins the match.

name: Rapid Fire
rules: The first team to hit a specified number of kills win. Eliminate the enemy to quickly activate Operator Skills, Scorestreaks, and limitless ammo.

name: 1v1 Duel
rules: In the first rount, players can fight with the weapons in their loadouts. The player who loses the round can designate a weapon type in the next round for both sides. Weapons not within the designated type will be replaced.

name: Capture the Flag
rules: Two rounds in total. Changes sides in each round. The team that captures the enemy's flag three times, or has the most flags when the round ends wins. The final battle result will be determined by the total captured flags. Overtime starts if two teams have the same number of flags after two rounds. Only when the flag is in our base can we capture the enemy's flag to score.

name: Attack of the Undead
rules:
Survivor: Survive at all costs to win. The last survivor will e given significantly more health and a Death Machine with limited ammunition. (A Survivor will convert to the Undead after death.) 
The Undead: The Undead have limitless respawns. Signal Flares are set next to the respawn location. Operator skills grand silent movement and increase movement speed.

name: Super Attack of the Undead
rules:
Core gameplay is the same as Attack of the Undead. 
Unique upgrades are available in Super Attack of the Undead, which you can purchase with points. Become Undead to infect others or be a Survivor to struggle to the end! 
Earn points by fighting or opening an airdrop. Consume points to get an upgrade.

name: Juggernaut
rules: The Juggernaut game mode is set up with every other player against one opponent (who is selected by random to be the first juggernaut). Everybody else must try to kill the Juggernaut; the player that ultimately kills the Juggernaut becomes the new Juggernaut. The Juggernaut's goal is to keep their position for as long as possible.

name: Ground War
rules:
Two factions compete to capture and hold multiple locations. The first faction to reach the target score wins. 
You can choose locations to respawn, drive vehicles, and fight for victory with 12 teammates.

name: Headquarters
rules:
Two factions must capture the HQ when it respawns. The faction that successfully captures the HQ needs to hold it until the defending time is over. Each second scores a point. 
There will be prep time before the next HQ respawns. It will be available when the countdown is complete. 
The defending faction cannot respawn until the HQ is destroyed or successfully defended.

name: Hardcore Team Deathmatch
rules:
Kill enemy players and take the lead. Be the first to reach the specified number of kills to win. 
Caution: Low health, no health recovery, no killcam, limited HU and friendly fire damage.

name: Hardcore Domination
rules:
Two factions compete to capture and hold three locations. Each time an objective is captured, the faction will get 1 point after a period of time; the first team to reach the target score wins. 
Caution: Low health, no health recovery, no killcam, limited HU and friendly fire damage.

name: Hardcore Hardpoint
rules:
Two factions compete to capture a Hardpoint. When there are only players from the same faction inside the Hardpoint zone, this faction will score 1 point each second. The hardpoint will relocate to a new position after a period of time. The faction that reaches the specified score limit wins. 
Caution: Low health, no health recovery, no killcam, limited HU and friendly fire damage.

name: Cranked
rules: The gametype is similar to Team Deathmatch with two teams competing to earn kills. Whenever a player gets a kill, they earn a "Cranked" bonus, giving them faster movement speed, reload, and ADS. Upon getting the bonus, the player is given a 30 second timer. After each kill or assist the player earns, the timer will reset. If the player fails to get a kill or assist within the time limit, they will explode and die.

name: Grind
rules: 5 vs 5. Collect dog tags and deliver them to the objective. Every dog tag delivered successfully scores you one point. The first team to reach the target score wins.

name: Guns Blazing
rules:
8-player FFA. Each kill earns you 1 point. The first team to reach the target score wins. 
Every time you kill or die, your rage value increases by 100. At 500, you become a Super Soldier. 
In the Super Soldier state, you will get a Chopper akimbo weapon that increases your HP to 300.

name: Cranked Confirmed
rules:
The core gameplay is the same as Cranked. 
Killed players drop dog tags. Enemy dog tags are outlined in red while friendly dog tags are outlined in blue. Collecting enemy dog tags scores points. The first team to reach target number of dog tags wins. Collecting enemy dog tags confirms the kill. Collecting friendly dog tags denies the enemy's kill.

name: Ground Missions
rules: Two factions compete to capture and hold five locations. Each time an objective is captured, the seizing faction will get 1 point. The first faction to reach the target score wins.

name: Drop Zone
rules: Capture the Drop Zone and open Care Packages.

name: Snowball Scuffle
rules:
10 vs 10. Collect snowmen and deliver them to the objective. Every snowman delivered successfully scores you one point. The first team to reach the target score wins. 
Pick up the Gift Boxes randomy scattered on the ground and receive special Operator Skills and Throwables.

name: Big Head Blizzard
rules:
You will always spawn at your base. Watch out for headshots! 
Blizzard Beasts can see the location of all players, but are visible to other players, too. 
Weapon balance adjustment: Headshot damage and the damage of some weapons has been adjusted. 
Levelin up unlocks your passive skills and increases HP. Once max level is reached, you become a Blizzard Beast. The final round starts when a team has 3 Blizzard Beasts or time runs out. The opposing team can also hae 3 Blizzard Beasts if they reach max level during the final round. 
Eliminating enemies earns you the most energy. Dealing enemy damage or healing your teammates by shooting them earns you less energy. You will lose energy upon death unless at max level. Once enough players have reached max level, they will transform into Blizzard Beasts. 
During the final round, all players only get 1 life. The last surviving team with the most players left is the winner.

name: Goliath Clash!
rules:
Suit up in the Goliath and use your firepower to capture the objectives. This mode is 5v5 and in TPP. 
Capturing points, defeating enemies, and collecting batteries will make your Goliath more powerful. 
Choose the Goliath type that suits your playstyle.

name: Chaos Control
rules: Capture the objectoves to win. You have infinite lives.

name: Search & Rescue
rules:
Core gameplay is the same as Search & Destroy. 
Players drop their holo dog tag after their first daeth in each round. 
Find the Holo Dog ags of your teammates, and you can revive them back into the current round. 
Revive your fallen teammates, and get back in the fight.

name: Arena
rules:
Players have to earn tokens by defeating enemies and completing objectives to earn tokens. These tokens can then be used to purchase weapons to carry into the map with you.
The interesting part of the new mode is that there will be a zone shrinking the map. Players have to take down the other two teams to achieve victory.
Its a round-based game mode and the first team to reach two rounds will achieve victory.

name: Safeguard
rules:
In Safeguard, there is an offensive and defensive team. The offensive team has to escort a non-combative robot along a predetermined path to a designated objective, typically near the defensive team's spawn point. The defensive team must prevent the robot from entering this objective. 
The team will get a point if they completed their objective that round (escorted the robot to the objective, or prevented the robot from entering the objective).

name: Ground War: Breach
rules: The Objective is the attacker as Phantom Corps needs to push until they conquer the map while the defender as The Tontine needs to defend and reinforce the location.

name: Boost Assault
rules:
Kill enemy players and take the lead. Be the first to reach the specified number of kills to win. 
Every player has exo suits capable of boosting their jump heigh, and sliding speed. Wall-running is also a movement mechanic.

name: Dropkick
rules:
Two teams fight over control of a briefcase and score points by keeping possession of it. 
Players of the team currently holding the briefcase will not respawn until it's dropped. 
The location of the player holding the briefcase is visible to all players. 
Players holding the briefcase can only use specific weapons, and cannot use Throwables, Scorestreas, or Operator Skills.

name: Quick Solo
rules: Core gameplay is the same as Team Deathmatch. The only difference is it's only 1v1 and the kill limit is 20. A unique feature is the ability to ban weapon types from being used.

name: Uplink
rules: To be added.

name: Hordepoint
rules: To be added.
